    Use Actions.release()

    Use Actions.click(WebElement)
    org.openqa.selenium.interactions.ClickAndHoldAction
    Use Actions.clickAndHold(WebElement)
    org.openqa.selenium.interactions.ContextClickAction
    Use Actions.contextClick(WebElement)

    The RC interface will be removed in Selenium 3.0. Please migrate to using WebDriver.
    org.openqa.selenium.interactions.DoubleClickAction
    Use Actions.doubleClick(WebElement)
    com.thoughtworks.selenium.HttpCommandProcessor
    The RC interface will be removed in Selenium 3.0. Please migrate to using WebDriver.
    org.openqa.selenium.json.JsonToBeanConverter
    Visibility will be reduced. Use Json.toType(Object, Type).

    Use Json.toType(Object, Type).

  • Deprecated Methods 
    Method and Description
    org.openqa.selenium.firefox.FirefoxOptions.addCapabilities(Capabilities)
    Use FirefoxOptions.merge(Capabilities).
    org.openqa.selenium.firefox.FirefoxOptions.addTo(DesiredCapabilities)
    Use MutableCapabilities.merge(Capabilities).
    org.openqa.selenium.remote.http.HttpClient.close()
    This responsibility moved to Factory
    org.openqa.selenium.safari.SafariDriverService.createDefaultService(SafariOptions)
    org.openqa.selenium.remote.http.HttpClient.execute(HttpRequest, boolean)
    All call sites found set followRedirects to true. Use HttpClient.execute(HttpRequest).
    org.openqa.selenium.chrome.ChromeOptions.getExperimentalOption(String)
    Getters are not needed in browser Options classes.
    org.openqa.selenium.firefox.FirefoxBinary.getExtraEnv()
    No replacement. Environment should be configured in DriverService instance.
    org.openqa.selenium.safari.SafariOptions.getPort()
    Getters are not needed in browser Options classes.
    org.openqa.selenium.safari.SafariOptions.getUseCleanSession()
    Getters are not needed in browser Options classes.
    org.openqa.selenium.safari.SafariOptions.getUseTechnologyPreview()
    Getters are not needed in browser Options classes.
    org.openqa.selenium.Capabilities.isJavascriptEnabled()
    Use is(SUPPORTS_JAVASCRIPT) instead
    org.openqa.selenium.support.ui.ExpectedConditions.numberOfwindowsToBe(int)
    please use ExpectedConditions.numberOfWindowsToBe(int) instead
    org.openqa.selenium.remote.DesiredCapabilities.opera()
    Use #operaBlink
    org.openqa.selenium.remote.DesiredCapabilities.phantomjs()
    PhantomJS is no longer actively developed, and support will eventually be dropped.
    org.openqa.selenium.remote.service.DriverService.sendOutputTo(OutputStream)
    Visibility will be restricted to 'protected' soon.
    org.openqa.selenium.firefox.FirefoxBinary.setEnvironmentProperty(String, String)
    org.openqa.selenium.firefox.FirefoxOptions.setLogLevel(Level)
    Use FirefoxOptions.setLogLevel(FirefoxDriverLogLevel)
    org.openqa.selenium.safari.SafariOptions.setUseCleanSession(boolean)
    Use SafariOptions.useCleanSession(boolean) instead
    org.openqa.selenium.remote.RemoteWebDriver.startClient()
    No longer used, as behaviour is now in CommandExecutor instances.
    org.openqa.selenium.remote.RemoteWebDriver.startClient(Capabilities)
    No longer used, as behaviour is now in CommandExecutor instances.
    org.openqa.selenium.remote.RemoteWebDriver.stopClient()
    No longer used, as behaviour is now in CommandExecutor instances.
    org.openqa.selenium.remote.RemoteWebDriver.stopClient(Capabilities)
    No longer used, as behaviour is now in CommandExecutor instances.
    org.openqa.selenium.support.ui.ExpectedConditions.textToBePresentInElement(By, String)
    Use ExpectedConditions.textToBePresentInElementLocated(By, String) instead
    org.openqa.selenium.firefox.FirefoxOptions.toCapabilities()
    No replacement. We are already Capabilities.
